title: Love Island's Jessie risks a wardrobe malfunction in barely-there swimsuit duration workout
text:
The cast of Love Island Australia regularly soak up the sunshine by lounging around the Fiji villa in their swimwear.

And on Tuesday's episode, Jessie Wynter appeared to go straight from the sun bed to working out in a barely-there swimsuit.

Leaving little to the imagination, the blonde bombshell flaunted her assets in a racy low-cut leotard as she performed exercises with partner Eoghan Murphy.

Scroll down for video

Would YOU wear this to workout in? Love Island's Jessie Wynter (above) risks a wardrobe malfunction in barely-there swimsuit while exercising with Eoghan

Jessie, who was a Miss Universe Australia 2019 finalist, risked a wardrobe malfunction as she moved in the daring design.

Not only did the red Baywatch-inspired one piece with cut-outs highlight her cleavage, it also showed off her taut stomach and pert derriere.

Jessie used a resistance band and a pair of blue dumbbells in the short clip shown on screen.

Forget to pack your activewear? Jessie used a resistance band and a pair of blue dumbbells as she worked out in the racy red swimsuit

Sweaty-yet-stylish: Working up a sweat on the villa's grassy lawn, she chose to place her blonde hair up in a chic low ponytail and wore a pair of dangling ear rings

Working up a sweat on the villa's grassy lawn, she chose to place her blonde hair up in a stylish low ponytail and wore a pair of dangling ear rings.

It's uncertain if Jessie packed activewear for her appearance on the show.

Meanwhile, her partner Eoghan was prepared for the workout session in active shorts, a white T-shirt, hat and sneakers.

Dressed to impress? Meanwhile, Jessie's partner Eoghan was prepared for the workout session in active shorts, a white T-shirt, hat and sneakers

While Jessie only made her debut on Love Island Australia last week, the star was a well-known Instagram influencer before appearing on the show.

Since appearing on the show, her following has grown to 67,000 followers and is one of this season's most-followed contestants remain in the villa.

Intruder Anna McEvoy has the biggest following by fans so far, with a whopping 92,000 followers on Instagram.

Love Island Australia airs weeknights from 8.30pm on Channel Nine
